COMMON ORDER 

[Order of this Court was made by R.SUBBIAH, J] 

W.P. No.8180 of 2019 has been filed seeking a direction to 

respondents 1 and 2 to evacuate the third respondent in encroachments 

2/6 

http://www.judis.nic.in 


Writ Petition Nos.8180 & 21436 of 2019 

of the general path and to ensure the petitioner to utilise the same to 

cultivate her land based upon her representation dated 28.08.2018. 

W.P. No.21436 of 2019 has been filed challenging the impugned 

Proceedings Ka.No.01/2018/U.Pe dated 12.07.2019 issued by the first 

respondent and seeking a direction to the first respondent to survey the 

entire extent of the property comprised in Survey No.217 at Romapuri 

Village, Cuddalore District and other lands which are encroached by the 

second respondent and others and to pass appropriate orders after 

providing sufficient opportunity to the petitioner and others. 

2.Since the issue involved in both the writ petitions are common, 

these are intertwined and disposed of by way of common order with the 

consent of either side. 

3.The facts of the case in W.P. No.8180 of 2019 are that the 

petitioner has been cultivating her land, situated at 30 feet road, near 

NHAI Road and that the general pathway belongs to NHAI, has been used 

for reaching the petitioner's land. The grievance of the petitioner is that 

the land of respondents 3 and 4 is situated near to her land and they have 

been occupying the general pathway by preventing the petitioner from 

entering and cultivating her land. In this regard, the petitioner has made a 

3/6 

http://www.judis.nic.in 


Writ Petition Nos.8180 & 21436 of 2019 

representation to respondents 1 and 2 on 04.07.2018 to take necessary 

action against the third respondent for removing the encroachment made 

by respondents 3 and 4 in the government land. Since no action was 

taken against them, the petitioner is before this Court. 

4.The facts of the case in W.P. No.21436 of 2019 are that in the 

year 2006, the government had issued patta to several persons in Survey 

No.172/15 Ramapuri Village, Cuddalore District to an extent of 32.50 ares 

under the scheme of landless people by order dated 14.09.2006. After the 

assignment, the petitioner and others are enjoying the above said land 

without any hindrance by constructing a small house in a portion of the 

said land. While so, the second respondent is having a land in S.No.38/4 

adjoining the petitioner's land in S.No.172/15 and by way of encroaching 

the Highways land, she constructed a building in the above said highways 

property in S.No.217 and the said property has been let out for rent to 

third parties and thereby, she has been earning monthly income of 

Rs.35,000/-. In order to harass the petitioner, the second respondent had 

filed a suit in O.S. No.53 of 2003 before the District Munsif-cum-Judicial 

Magistrate, Neyveli seeking relief for declaration and permanent injunction 

as against the petitioner and others with respect to the above said 

property. By judgment and decree dated 02.07.2013, the District Munsif 

cum Judicial Magistrate dismissed the said suit. As against the same, the 

