second respondent has filed an Appeal in A.S. No.1 of 2015 before the 

Subordinate Judge, Neyveli and the same was also dismissed by judgment 

and decree dated 24.07.2015. Suppressing the above facts, the second 

respondent has filed the above writ petition in W.P. No.8180 of 2019 

before this Court to evict the petitioner. While so, the first respondent has 

issued the above proceedings only on the inducement of the second 

respondent. Therefore, the petitioner is before this Court challenging the 

same and seeking the above direction. 

5.Heard the learned counsel for the petitioners, learned 

Government Advocate and the learned counsel for R3 and R4 and perused 

the materials on record. 

6.Considering the submissions made by both sides, we are of the 

opinion that the issue involved in both the writ petitions is nothing, but a 

disputed question of facts. As the same cannot be agitated before this 

Court, we are constrained to direct the Assistant Engineer, National 

Highways, Vridhachalam, Cuddalore District to conduct an enquiry and 

survey the said lands in the presence of the parties, by issuing notice to 

both the petitioners as well as the fourth respondent in W.P. No.8180 of 

2019. After enquiry, if he comes to the conclusion that there was an 

encroachment made in the above lands, he is further directed to remove 

